<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Description ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''Arch StructuresFromSelection''' tool creates multiple [[Arch_Structure|structure]] objects from a base object, using selected edges as extrusion paths.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Usage ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select a 2D base object ([[Arch_Profile|profile]], [[Sketcher_Workbench#Profile_sketches|sketch]], face or closed Draft object).
# Select the edges you want to use as extrusion paths.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Utils → Structure Tools → [[Image:Arch_MultipleStructures.svg|16px]] Multiple Structures}} option from the menu.
# For each selected edge a structure object is created.
</div>


